                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.12 Gomez and Rubio/51: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-25T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 25, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>183. Your 213, June 23, 1 p.m. The Department was informed this; morning by
                    telephone from the Governor of Oklahoma that the expenses of Salvador Cortés
                    Rubio would be fully taken care of.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
